patch file for above description

Hello All,

   In reviewing 'test_limit.c' in httpd-2.4.3/tests, I found an instance
of bcopy() which is deprecated and bzero() which is deprecated which the patch file below replaces with memmove() and memset():

--- test_limits.c.orig	2012-12-21 16:41:40.670528588 -0800
+++ test_limits.c	2012-12-21 16:44:02.483550214 -0800
@@ -124,8 +124,8 @@
         perror("gethostbyname");
         exit(1);
     }
-    bzero(&sin, sizeof(sin));
-    bcopy(he->h_addr, (char *)&sin.sin_addr, he->h_length);
+    memset(&sin, 0, sizeof(sin)); /* bzero() deprecated, replaced with memset() */
+    memmove((char *)&sin.sin_addr, be->h_addr, he->h_length);
     sin.sin_family = he->h_addrtype;
     sin.sin_port = htons(port);

Please feel free to make any changes or comments to the above
patch file.

Bill Parker (wp02855 at gmail dot com)
